<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">sobe</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Well lets start with the raves:<P>Looks Great<BR>Decent AC since Patch<P>Now the gripes:<BR>Stats could be better... a bit higher pluses to saves would be nice.<P>I said it in another post now here... Have the ability to create small Cleic Armor; much like Warrior's Crafted.  And better yet, I'm stretching, make the NPC who does it Dark Elf ;-)<P>Please give me some opinions on this subject.<P><P>------------------<BR>Sobe I'vengeance<BR>House I'vengeance<BR>Tier'Dal Cleric</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Boanerges</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I used to think like you do, Sobe.<P>I wondered why the pallys got 14 wisdom from their armor while we got only 10. I wondered why we got such seemingly useless stats like +int and +dex. But then Gordon... or was it Brad?... I can't remember... anyways, they posted what stats do what and I can see why the cleric armor now includes those stats.<P>For the most part the quest armor is to fill that void between bronze and planes armor.<P>IF you are going to start this whole debate again realize a few things first:<P>1. Realize Gordon thinks the matter is closed and he has stated openly that he is satisfied with the stats the way they are. Changing his mind is an uphill battle all the way.<P>2. Focus on only ONE major issue. If you try to mention several things at once the Gordon2000 processor will shutdown due to an illegal operation(2 requests, no matter how related, cannot be processed at once). Either pick the resists issue (a good one to be sure. +5 per resist is not that much) or pick the wisdom issue (ie better distribution across the set instead of dumping it into one piece) which is another valid issue.<P>Anyways, just 2cp...<P>------------------<BR>Boanerges Thundercry<BR>Erudite Cleric of Prexus<BR>Proud member of The Steel Wind<BR>Cazic Thule Server<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Seliris</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Just to throw a little statistics in the fray.<BR>(I wear all pieces but one bracer (have an RMB) and the shield.(have a CGS))<P>Although the armor is a little heavy, it isnt has heavy as bronze, so there is a plus.<BR>(Humans and dwarves tend to not worry about that)<P>AC is WAY better.<BR>(wisdom of 160 with a 735 AC here)<P>It looks pretty good on most races.<BR>(for those who are fashion oriented)<P>Plus... at least in my case, when I tell people that Seliris is my only char, and I earned all my pieces (originally paid to do a dual quest for BP, but have since done it again by myself) People generally know you are a person who doesnt give up easily.<P>My 2cp<P>------------------<BR>-Seliris Caileadair<BR>High Cleric of Clachan Brigh<BR>Bristlebane Server<BR>*i dont get angry at the game, just the people playing it*<P><BR><p>[This message has been edited by Seliris (edited 05-02-2000).]</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
